## Automated first-pass reviewer (advisory)

When a PR touches any of these paths, the workflow `.github/workflows/claude-review-heavy-lane.yml` (rendered into the consumer repo in dev-system stage D0e) posts a first-pass review comment with a verdict of `PASS` / `REQUEST_CHANGES` / `NEEDS_OPERATOR_REVIEW`. The workflow is **advisory / review-only** — `contents: read` and `pull-requests: write` permissions ONLY, never `contents: write`. It cannot commit, push, auto-fix, or auto-merge.

The operator remains the final gate. A `VERDICT: PASS` is necessary but not sufficient for merge; the §1 pipeline above is unchanged. Review mode for this project: `{{ review_mode }}`.

The workflow's `paths:` filter equals exactly `groups.heavy_lane ∪ groups.claude_system` from `.claude/path_registry.yaml`; drift in either direction reds CI via `scripts/check_manifests.py`.
